{
  "texts": [
    "The sole task of the GPT is to predict the next token in the sequence.",
    "GPT-2 was designed to predict the next sentence in sentences and establishes that language models can learn tasks without direct supervision.",
    "The GPT-3 model scales up on the GPT-2 model even further with 175 billion trainable parameters.",
    "Its model architecture is the same as that of the GPT-2 except that the transformer layers have alternating dense and locally banded sparse attention patterns.",
    "GPT-4 most likely uses 100 Trillion parameters (Karhade 2022)."
  ]
}